metadata.name: Petal 3D #5
metadata.description:
This project features an abstract, multi-layered structure that resembles a blooming flower or organic shape. The composition is characterized by overlapping translucent forms that create a sense of depth and fluidity. The colors blend seamlessly, adding to the ethereal and dynamic quality. The use of gradients and transparency enhances the three-dimensional effect, giving the piece an almost holographic nature, a fusion of organic and mathematical aesthetics.

Made of five constant height bands perpendicular to the surface of a sphere. Position, RGB values and transparency of the bands are governed by the control points of closed loop Bezier curves.

Press [1/2/4] to redraw at 800/1600/3200 px resolution.
Press [s] to save a png at the current resolution.

100% code-generated artwork, written in javascript using the p5.js library.

AndersB 2025

metadata.name: Spring flowers #N #1
metadata.description:
“Spring flowers” is a generative art series conceived in Kyiv in March 2025, under the tender influence of the city’s blooming spring. This work captures the delicate essence of renewal and the vibrant pulse of nature awakening, drawing inspiration from Andy Warhol’s iconic Flowers series. Like Warhol’s bold yet playful exploration of floral forms, this series reimagines blossoms through a digital lens, infusing them with a soft, watercolor effect that evokes the gentle breath of spring in Kyiv.

Each piece unfolds as a unique composition of five abstract flowers, their petals painted with fluid, translucent hues—vibrant corals, sunny yellows, serene blues, and lush greens—set against a subtle, pastel background. The black centers of the flowers, fading into airy grays, mimic the organic diffusion of watercolor on paper, while animated particles drift across the canvas, embodying the breeze that carries spring’s promise. This interplay of stillness and motion reflects the harmony of nature’s cycles, blending algorithmic precision with the spontaneity of hand-painted art.

Why Collect?
Unique Generative Creations: Every artwork is algorithmically distinct, offering collectors an exclusive piece of digital flora.

*Warholian Echoes: A modern nod to Andy Warhol’s Flowers, merging pop art legacy with cutting-edge generative techniques.
*Kyiv’s Spring Spirit: Created amidst Kyiv’s blossoming season, it encapsulates a moment of beauty and resilience.
*Own a piece of “Spring flowers”  — a celebration of spring’s fleeting magic, rooted in Kyiv’s vibrant soul and the timeless allure of watercolor blooms.

***
Press S or double-click to save as PNG.

***

Kyiv, 17.03.2025

metadata.name: Circumscript #4
metadata.description:
It has always been a goal of mine to incorporate the worlds of physical and digital art together in a piece. And with circumscript I am the closest I've ever been. Circumscript uses a custom shader written to mix and "dilute" the colors on the canvas, thus creating a very physical feeling piece.

This dilution can be more or less depending on the edition, but always plays a huge role in the feel of the piece.


Happy new year.


----


[m] or [double tap] : opens the export/settings menu, use this menu to change the resolution, and make sure to press the reload button if you do.
[holding down] : zooms in on a certain area of the piece, depending on where your mouse/finger is. Use this feature to expore the complex textures of the piece in more detail, it's highly recommended to do this on a higher resolution setting.

The outputs can vary slighty per device, as there's a slight difference in how certain math gets interpreted on different devices with shaders.


----


Made with p5.js and webgl by Wouter Missler in 2022/3.

metadata.name: meios #255
Reflejos #31
metadata.description:
Reflejos es un proyecto de arte generativo diseñado para existir en la blockchain de Tezos. Este proyecto se aloja en la plataforma fx(hash) y genera obras de arte únicas utilizando un algoritmo y un sistema numérico hexadecimal que se crea con cada nuevo token.

Este proyecto fue desarrollado utilizando la librería p5.js de JavaScript, creada por Lauren Lee McCarthy. Reflejos es el resultado de la interacción entre la percepción humana y un conjunto de reglas interpretadas por la máquina.

Inspirado por la experiencia de caminar junto al mar y los estados de calma y contemplación que esta actividad puede evocar, Reflejos busca entrelazar a los espectadores con las obras de la colección. 

La intención es motivar al espectador a explorar su interior y descubrir momentos de apertura perceptiva. 

El objetivo es que la obra provoque una sensación de calma y claridad en el espectador a través de una conexión íntima y personal.

metadata.name: Proxima #117
metadata.description:
The preparations for the first mission began in 2142. It had become clear that mining petroleum on Earth would soon become financially unfeasible, so looking to other planets was the only logical choice. It took seventeen more years to perfect the technology so that the first colonists could reach Proxima b within the lifetime of one generation.

After 45 years of travelling at almost one-tenth of the speed of light, they reached their new home. It was rich in petrochemicals but scarce in the nutrients necessary for long term human survival. After merely six generations, humanity was forced to travel once again in search of a new world. The four missions that parted from the Proxima system to colonise other possibly habitable planets in the galaxy sparked a new age of human civilisation that would never see itself united and thriving again.

Eventually, all the colonies became independent societies as their differing interests drove them apart. Each small civilisation chose its path, wandering the void of space alone. Over time, millions of kilometres apart, each colony developed its own culture and traditions. While their habits and customs changed, some things remained the same across all the societies, like how it became a certain tradition to convert the outer world years and days to Earth time and celebrate holidays according to the calendar of the old world.

The new nomads learned from the first pilgrims. They used the technology once optimised for oil extraction to traverse other worlds, searching for sustenance. Peculiar wandering nonspaces emerged from the involuntary degrowth of human civilisation.

-----

Click on the image to open the menu. You may choose the quality from preview to the resolution of a print of approximately 30cm in height. In live mode, click on PNG to save the rendered image.
Depending on the device and CPU usage, it takes from a few seconds (on fast computers) to a minute (sometimes more) on mid-tier phones to render the image.

Requirements: 1GB of RAM. The system needs up to 200 MB of free RAM for rendering square preview images and up to 400 MB of free RAM for rendering square images at the highest resolution. We tested on Chrome, Safari, Firefox, Edge / Windows, Mac OS, Android, and iPhone, but please make sure it works on your device before minting.

Original piece by mrkswcz and Ismahelio. Made with Three.js. 

San Sebastian - Madrid. May 2022.
